Assignment 4 Prepared by Francis. Batch DS2312¶

Import Library¶

In [1]:
import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

Q1.¶

In [2]:
# Specify the URL
url = 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_most-viewed_YouTube_videos'
In [3]:
# Send a GET request to the URL
response = requests.get(url)
In [4]:
# Check if the request was successful (status code 200)
if response.status_code == 200:
    # Parse the HTML content of the page
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')
In [5]:
soup

<div aria-labelledby="firstHeading" class="vector-body" data-mw-ve-target-container="" id="bodyContent">
<div class="vector-body-before-content">
<div class="mw-indicators">
<div class="mw-indicator" id="mw-indicator-pp-default"><div class="mw-parser-output"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Protection_policy#semi" title="This article is semi-protected due to vandalism"><img alt="Page semi-protected" class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="512" data-file-width="512" decoding="async" height="20" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/1b/Semi-protection-shackle.svg/20px-Semi-protection-shackle.svg.png" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/1b/Semi-protection-shackle.svg/30px-Semi-protection-shackle.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/1b/Semi-protection-shackle.svg/40px-Semi-protection-shackle.svg.png 2x" width="20"/></a></span></div></div>
</div>
<div class="noprint" id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
</div>
<div id="contentSub"><div id="mw-content-subtitle"></div></div>
<div class="mw-body-content" id="mw-content-text"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" dir="ltr" lang="en"><p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p>
<style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r1033289096">.mw-parser-output .hatnote{font-style:italic}.mw-parser-output div.hatnote{padding-left:1.6em;margin-bottom:0.5em}.mw-parser-output .hatnote i{font-style:normal}.mw-parser-output .hatnote+link+.hatnote{margin-top:-0.5em}</style><div class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable" role="note">This is a <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Lists#Dynamic_lists" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Lists">dynamic list</a> and may never be able to satisfy particular standards for completeness. You can help by <a href="/wiki/Special:EditPage/List_of_most-viewed_YouTube_videos" title="Special:EditPage/List of most-viewed YouTube videos">adding missing items</a> with <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Reliable_sources" title="Wikipedia:Reliable sources">reliable sources</a>.</div>
<p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p><p><a href="/wiki/YouTube" title="YouTube">YouTube</a> is an American video-sharing website headquartered in <a href="/wiki/San_Bruno,_California" title="San Bruno, California">San Bruno, California</a>. Although the most-viewed videos were initially <a href="/wiki/Viral_video" title="Viral video">viral videos</a>, such as "<a href='/wiki/Judson_Laipply#"Evolution_of_Dance"' title="Judson Laipply">Evolution of Dance</a>" and "<a href="/wiki/Charlie_Bit_My_Finger" title="Charlie Bit My Finger">Charlie Bit My Finger</a>", the most-viewed videos were increasingly related to <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Music_videos" title="Music videos">music videos</a>. Since <a href="/wiki/Lady_Gaga" title="Lady Gaga">Lady Gaga</a>'s "<a href="/wiki/Bad_Romance" title="Bad Romance">Bad Romance</a>" in 2009, every video that has reached the top of the "most-viewed YouTube videos" list has been a music video. Some of the previously most-viewed videos are no longer available on the site.
</p><p>In November 2005, a <a href="/wiki/Nike,_Inc." title="Nike, Inc.">Nike</a> advertisement featuring Brazilian football player <a href="/wiki/Ronaldinho" title="Ronaldinho">Ronaldinho</a> became the first video to reach 1,000,000 views.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-1"><a href="#cite_note-1">[1]</a></sup> The billion-view mark was first passed by <a href="/wiki/Gangnam_Style" title="Gangnam Style">Gangnam Style</a> in December 2012. On January 13, 2022, <a href="/wiki/Pinkfong" title="Pinkfong">Pinkfong</a>'s "<a href="/wiki/Baby_Shark" title="Baby Shark">Baby Shark</a>" became the first video to hit 10,000,000,000 views.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-2"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup>
</p><p>Views represent how many times a video is watched. To ensure that traffic is coming from actual humans and not scripts or other deceptive methods, YouTube has a secret algorithm to separate legitimate views from illegitimate ones, and only legitimate views are included in the view count.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup> <span class="citation-needed-content" style="padding-left:0.1em; padding-right:0.1em; color:#595959; border:1px solid #DDD;">Specifically, to count as a legitimate view, a user must intentionally initiate the playback of the video and play at least 30 seconds of the video (or the entire video for shorter videos). Additionally, while replays count as views, there is a limit of 4 or 5 views per IP address during a 24-hour period, after which point, no further views from that IP are counted until the 24-hour period expires.</span><sup class="noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style="margin-left:0.1em; white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources. (January 2024)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup> <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup>
</p>
<meta property="mw:PageProp/toc">

<p>The following table lists the top 30 most-viewed videos on <a href="/wiki/YouTube" title="YouTube">YouTube</a>, with each total rounded to the nearest 10 million views, uploader, and publication date. Note that some videos may not be available worldwide due to <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Geolocation_software#Regional_licensing" title="Geolocation software">regional restrictions</a> in certain countries.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup>

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Billion-View_Club">Billion-View Club</span></h2>
<p>An early metric of a video's popularity was the so-called Billion-View Club, denoting videos which had succeeded in reaching over 1 billion views since their initial upload.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-RollingStone_60-0"><a href="#cite_note-RollingStone-60">[55]</a></sup>
</p><p>In December 2012, "<a href="/wiki/Gangnam_Style_(music_video)" title="Gangnam Style (music video)">Gangnam Style</a>" became the first video to reach one billion views.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-billboardbillion_37-1"><a href="#cite_note-billboardbillion-37">[33]</a></sup> By June 2015, only "<a href="/wiki/Baby_(Justin_Bieber_song)#Music_video" title="Baby (Justin Bieber song)">Baby</a>" had also managed to pass this threshold, but, by October 2015, a total of ten videos had done so,<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-RollingStone_60-1"><a href="#cite_note-RollingStone-60">[55]</a></sup> and the number grew further to over 200 in February 2022.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-61"><a href="#cite_note-61">[56]</a></sup> Considering older videos that pre-dated YouTube's foundation in 2005 but were added later:
</p>
<ul><li>"<a href="/wiki/November_Rain" title="November Rain">November Rain</a>" by <a href="/wiki/Guns_N%27_Roses" title="Guns N' Roses">Guns N' Roses</a> became the first video made prior to 2005, YouTube's foundation year, to reach this threshold by July 2018.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-62"><a href="#cite_note-62">[57]</a></sup></li>
<li>"<a href="/wiki/Numb_(Linkin_Park_song)" title="Numb (Linkin Park song)">Numb</a>" by <a href="/wiki/Linkin_Park" title="Linkin Park">Linkin Park</a> was the first 2000s video predating YouTube to reach 1 billion views in November 2018.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-63"><a href="#cite_note-63">[58]</a></sup></li>
<li>"<a href="/wiki/Bohemian_Rhapsody" title="Bohemian Rhapsody">Bohemian Rhapsody</a>" by <a href="/wiki/Queen_(band)" title="Queen (band)">Queen</a> was the first 1970s video (and pre-1990s video) to reach 1 billion views in July 2019.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-64"><a href="#cite_note-64">[59]</a></sup></li>
<li>"<a href="/wiki/Sweet_Child_o%27_Mine" title="Sweet Child o' Mine">Sweet Child o' Mine</a>" by Guns N' Roses was the first 1980s video to reach 1 billion views in October 2019.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-65"><a href="#cite_note-65">[60]</a></sup></li></ul>
<p>With numerous videos readily clearing one billion views by 2018, more interest has been on two- and three-billion-views-and-higher metrics. In May 2014, "Gangnam Style" became the first video to exceed two billion views.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-billboardbillion2_38-1"><a href="#cite_note-billboardbillion2-38">[34]</a></sup> "<a href="/wiki/Despacito#Music_video" title="Despacito">Despacito</a>" became the first video to reach three billion views in August 2017,<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3billion_12-1"><a href="#cite_note-3billion-12">[11]</a></sup> four billion in October 2017,<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4billion_13-1"><a href="#cite_note-4billion-13">[12]</a></sup> five billion in April 2018,<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5billion_14-1"><a href="#cite_note-5billion-14">[13]</a></sup> six billion in February 2019,<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-6billion_15-1"><a href="#cite_note-6billion-15">[14]</a></sup> and seven billion in October 2020.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-7billion_16-1"><a href="#cite_note-7billion-16">[15]</a></sup> "<a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Baby_Shark_Dance" title="Baby Shark Dance">Baby Shark Dance</a>" became the first video to reach eight billion views in February 2021, nine billion views in July 2021, and ten billion views in January 2022.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-Baby_Shark_Ten_Billion_7-1"><a href="#cite_note-Baby_Shark_Ten_Billion-7">[7]</a></sup> As of May 2023, it has more than twelve billion views.
</p><p>As of May2023<sup class="plainlinks noexcerpt noprint asof-tag update" style="display:none;"><a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=List_of_most-viewed_YouTube_videos&amp;action=edit">[update]</a></sup>, thirteen videos have exceeded four billion views, eight of which exceed five billion views, five of which exceed six billion views, and two of which exceed eight billion views. "<a href="/wiki/See_You_Again" title="See You Again">See You Again</a>" became the second video to reach three billion views in August 2017,<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-SeeYouAgain3_28-1"><a href="#cite_note-SeeYouAgain3-28">[25]</a></sup> followed by "Gangnam Style" in November 2017.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-Gangnam3_39-1"><a href="#cite_note-Gangnam3-39">[35]</a></sup> "<a href="/wiki/Shape_of_You#Music_video" title="Shape of You">Shape of You</a>" became the second video to reach four billion views in January 2019,<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-ShapeofYou4_22-1"><a href="#cite_note-ShapeofYou4-22">[20]</a></sup> followed by "See You Again" in February 2019.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-SeeYouAgain4_29-1"><a href="#cite_note-SeeYouAgain4-29">[26]</a></sup> "<a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Baby_Shark_Dance" title="Baby Shark Dance">Baby Shark Dance</a>" became the second video to reach five billion views in April 2020,<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-66"><a href="#cite_note-66">[61]</a></sup> followed by "Shape of You" in October 2020. "Baby Shark Dance" became the second video to reach six billion views in July 2020, and seven billion views in October 2020.
</p><p>The majority of these videos in the Billion-View Club have been commercial <a href="/wiki/Music_video" title="Music video">music videos</a> by popular artists, but the list has included oddities, typically programs aimed at children. Such videos include two episodes of the Russian animated cartoon <i><a href="/wiki/Masha_and_the_Bear" title="Masha and the Bear">Masha and the Bear</a></i>, a version of "<a href="/wiki/The_Wheels_on_the_Bus" title="The Wheels on the Bus">The Wheels on the Bus</a>" by the British animation studio <a href="/wiki/Little_Baby_Bum" title="Little Baby Bum">Little Baby Bum</a>, and "<a href="/wiki/Johnny_Johnny_Yes_Papa" title="Johnny Johnny Yes Papa">Johnny Johnny Yes Papa</a>" from children's stations LooLoo Kids and <a href="/wiki/ChuChu_TV" title="ChuChu TV">ChuChu TV</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-67"><a href="#cite_note-67">[62]</a></sup> Various versions of the song "<a href="/wiki/Baby_Shark" title="Baby Shark">Baby Shark</a>" in total amassed more than five billion views by January 2019, with the original version posted by <a href="/wiki/Pinkfong" title="Pinkfong">Pinkfong</a> having exceeded two billion views previously.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-68"><a href="#cite_note-68">[63]</a></sup> The original video by Pinkfong is now the most viewed video on the site. On October 29, 2020, Baby Shark surpassed 7 billion views, and on November 2, 2020, it passed Despacito to become the most viewed video on YouTube. On February 23, 2021, Baby Shark surpassed 8 billion views, becoming the first video to do so. On July 20, 2021, Baby Shark surpassed 9 billion views, becoming the first (and currently only) video to do so. On January 13, 2022, Baby Shark became the first (and currently only) video to surpass 10 billion views.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-Baby_Shark_Ten_Billion_7-2"><a href="#cite_note-Baby_Shark_Ten_Billion-7">[7]</a></sup>
</p><p>On July 14, 2022, YouTube made a special playlist and video celebrating the 317 music videos to have hit 1 billion views and joined the "Billion Views Club".<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-69"><a href="#cite_note-69">[64]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-70"><a href="#cite_note-70">[65]</a></sup>
</p>

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Other_milestones">Other milestones</span></h2>
<p>YouTube announced that cumulative views of videos related to <i><a href="/wiki/Minecraft" title="Minecraft">Minecraft</a></i>, some of which had been on the service as early as 2009, exceeded 1 trillion views on December 14, 2021, and was the most-watched video game content on the site.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-129"><a href="#cite_note-129">[116]</a></sup>
</p>

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span></h2>
<style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r1011085734">.mw-parser-output .reflist{font-size:90%;margin-bottom:0.5em;list-style-type:decimal}.mw-parser-output .reflist .references{font-size:100%;margin-bottom:0;list-style-type:inherit}.mw-parser-output .reflist-columns-2{column-width:30em}.mw-parser-output .reflist-columns-3{column-width:25em}.mw-parser-output .reflist-columns{margin-top:0.3em}.mw-parser-output .reflist-columns ol{margin-top:0}.mw-parser-output .reflist-columns li{page-break-inside:avoid;break-inside:avoid-column}.mw-parser-output .reflist-upper-alpha{list-style-type:upper-alpha}.mw-parser-output .reflist-upper-roman{list-style-type:upper-roman}.mw-parser-output .reflist-lower-alpha{list-style-type:lower-alpha}.mw-parser-output .reflist-lower-greek{list-style-type:lower-greek}.mw-parser-output .reflist-lower-roman{list-style-type:lower-roman}</style><div class="reflist reflist-upper-alpha">
<div class="mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns"><ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"Baby Shark Dance" was the fifth video to reach 4 billion views on November 25, 2019; second video to reach 5 billion views on April 3, 2020; second video to reach 6 billion views on July 16, 2020; second video to reach 7 billion views on October 29, 2020; first video to reach 8 billion views on February 23, 2021; the first video to reach 9 billion views on July 20, 2021; first video to reach 10 billion views on January 13, 2022;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-Baby_Shark_Ten_Billion_7-0"><a href="#cite_note-Baby_Shark_Ten_Billion-7">[7]</a></sup> first video to reach 11 billion views on July 24, 2022; the first video to reach 12 billion views on December 29, 2022, and the first video to reach 13 billion views on June 20, 2023. It surpassed "Despacito" on November 1, 2020 to become the most-viewed video of all time.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-8"><a href="#cite_note-8">[8]</a></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-despacitoview-18"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-despacitoview_18-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-despacitoview_18-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">"Despacito" surpassed "See You Again" as the most viewed video on August 4, 2017;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-Despacito_11-0"><a href="#cite_note-Despacito-11">[10]</a></sup> first video to reach 3 billion views on August 4, 2017;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3billion_12-0"><a href="#cite_note-3billion-12">[11]</a></sup> first video to reach 4 billion views on October 11, 2017;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4billion_13-0"><a href="#cite_note-4billion-13">[12]</a></sup> first video to reach 5 billion views on April 5, 2018;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5billion_14-0"><a href="#cite_note-5billion-14">[13]</a></sup> first video to reach 6 billion views on February 24, 2019;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-6billion_15-0"><a href="#cite_note-6billion-15">[14]</a></sup> first video to reach 7 billion views on October 10, 2020;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-7billion_16-0"><a href="#cite_note-7billion-16">[15]</a></sup> second video to reach 8 billion views on November 6, 2022.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-17"><a href="#cite_note-17">[16]</a></sup> YouTube's <a href="/wiki/List_of_most-liked_YouTube_videos" title="List of most-liked YouTube videos">most liked video</a> with over 52 million likes as of January2024<sup class="plainlinks noexcerpt noprint asof-tag update" style="display:none;"><a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=List_of_most-viewed_YouTube_videos&amp;action=edit">[update]</a></sup>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-24"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"Shape of You" was the second video to reach 4 billion views on January 7, 2019;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-ShapeofYou4_22-0"><a href="#cite_note-ShapeofYou4-22">[20]</a></sup> third video to reach 5 billion views on October 1, 2020; fifth video to reach 6 billion views on May 23, 2023.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-23"><a href="#cite_note-23">[21]</a></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-30"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"See You Again" surpassed "Gangnam Style" as the most viewed video on July 10, 2017;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-SeeYouAgaintop_26-0"><a href="#cite_note-SeeYouAgaintop-26">[23]</a></sup> second video to reach 2 billion views on September 3, 2016;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-27"><a href="#cite_note-27">[24]</a></sup> second video to reach 3 billion views on August 6, 2017;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-SeeYouAgain3_28-0"><a href="#cite_note-SeeYouAgain3-28">[25]</a></sup> third video to reach 4 billion views on February 7, 2019; fourth video to reach 5 billion views on March 9, 2021;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-SeeYouAgain4_29-0"><a href="#cite_note-SeeYouAgain4-29">[26]</a></sup> and the third <a href="/wiki/List_of_most-liked_YouTube_videos" title="List of most-liked YouTube videos">most liked video</a> with over 42 million likes as of January2024<sup class="plainlinks noexcerpt noprint asof-tag update" style="display:none;"><a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=List_of_most-viewed_YouTube_videos&amp;action=edit">[update]</a></sup>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-gangnamview-40"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-gangnamview_40-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-gangnamview_40-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">"Gangnam Style" surpassed "Baby" as the most viewed video on November 24, 2012;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-GangnamStyle_36-0"><a href="#cite_note-GangnamStyle-36">[32]</a></sup> first video to reach 1 billion views on December 21, 2012;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-billboardbillion_37-0"><a href="#cite_note-billboardbillion-37">[33]</a></sup> first video to reach 2 billion views on May 30, 2014;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-billboardbillion2_38-0"><a href="#cite_note-billboardbillion2-38">[34]</a></sup> third video to reach 3 billion views on November 25, 2017; eighth video to reach 4 billion views on March 4, 2021.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-Gangnam3_39-0"><a href="#cite_note-Gangnam3-39">[35]</a></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-75"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-75">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"Baby" became to first video to reach 500 million views on March 28, 2011.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-73"><a href="#cite_note-73">[68]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-74"><a href="#cite_note-74">[69]</a></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-80"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-80">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"Bad Romance" became the first video to reach 200 million views on May 9, 2010.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-78"><a href="#cite_note-78">[72]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-79"><a href="#cite_note-79">[73]</a></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-90"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-90">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Approximately ten million views per month as of 2007.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-89"><a href="#cite_note-89">[82]</a></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-96"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-96">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"Music is My Hot Hot Sex" became the first video to reach 100 million views on March 11, 2008.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-History2_95-0"><a href="#cite_note-History2-95">[87]</a></sup> The uploader then deleted the video four days later, and "Evolution of Dance" regained its status as the most-viewed video.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-MusicHotSexSydney_93-1"><a href="#cite_note-MusicHotSexSydney-93">[85]</a></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-98"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-98">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"Evolution of Dance" became the first video to reach 20 million views on June 5, 2006 and the first video to reach 50 million views on June 7, 2007, and received approximately five million views per month.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-History2_95-1"><a href="#cite_note-History2-95">[87]</a></sup> It is the only video on this list to hold the No. 1 spot on more than one occasion.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-104"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-104">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"Pokmon Theme Music Video" became the first video to reach 10 million views on May 6, 2006.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-History1_102-0"><a href="#cite_note-History1-102">[92]</a></sup> It was removed from YouTube in June 2007 for copyright infringement.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-103"><a href="#cite_note-103">[93]</a></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-115"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-115">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"Phony Photo Booth" became the first video to reach 5 million views on February 8, 2006.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-History1_102-1"><a href="#cite_note-History1-102">[92]</a></sup> It was removed from YouTube in February 1418, 2006 for terms of use violation.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-112"><a href="#cite_note-112">[101]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-113"><a href="#cite_note-113">[102]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-114"><a href="#cite_note-114">[103]</a></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-125"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-125">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"Ronaldinho: Touch of Gold" became the first video to reach 500,000 views on November 3, 2005;<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-122"><a href="#cite_note-122">[110]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-History1_102-2"><a href="#cite_note-History1-102">[92]</a></sup> first video to reach 2 million views on December 12, 2005.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-History1_102-3"><a href="#cite_note-History1-102">[92]</a></sup> It was removed from YouTube in JulyAugust 2009 for copyright infringement.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-123"><a href="#cite_note-123">[111]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-124"><a href="#cite_note-124">[112]</a></sup></span>
</li>

In [6]:
 # Find the table containing the most viewed YouTube videos
 table = soup.find('table', {'class': 'wikitable'})

 # Initialize lists to store the data
 ranks = []
 video_titles = []
 artists = []
 upload_dates = []
 views_counts = []
In [7]:
# Iterate through the rows of the table
for row in table.find_all('tr')[1:]:  # Skip the header row
        # Extract data from each column if there are enough columns
        columns = row.find_all('td')
        if len(columns) >= 5:
            rank = columns[0].text.strip()
            title = columns[1].text.strip()
            artist = columns[2].text.strip()
            upload_date = columns[4].text.strip()
            views = columns[3].text.strip()
In [8]:
# Append data to the lists
ranks.append(rank)
video_titles.append(title)
artists.append(artist)
upload_dates.append(upload_date)
views_counts.append(views)
In [9]:

      function googleTranslateElementInit() {
         if ($(window).width() < 760){
         new google.translate.TranslateElement({pageLanguage: 'en', includedLanguages: 'en,hi'}, 'google_translate_element_mob');
      }
         else{
            new google.translate.TranslateElement({pageLanguage: 'en', includedLanguages: 'en,hi'}, 'google_translate_element');
         } 
      }

      function setNavigationSession(key, value) {
         return false;
         $.ajax({
            url: "https://www.bcci.tv/set-session",
            type: "get",
            data: { 'key': key, 'value': value },
            success: function(response) {
               if (response.status) {
                  location.href="/";
               }
            },
            error: function(xhr) {
               
            }
         });
      }

      function setNavigationUrl(base_url = '') {
        let platform = $('.h_platform.active').data('platform');
         let type = $('.h_type.active').data('type');

         base_url = base_url ? base_url : 'https://www.bcci.tv';
         
         let url = base_url+'?platform='+platform+'&type='+type;
         console.log(url);
         window.location.href = url;

    $(document).on('click', '.copyUrl', function() {
        $(".ctc .c").text("Copied!");
        var shareurl = $(this).attr('data-share');
        var dummy = document.createElement("input");
        dummy.value = shareurl;
        document.body.appendChild(dummy);
        dummy.select();
        dummy.focus();
        document.execCommand('copy');            
        document.body.removeChild(dummy);     
    });

        $(".ctc .c").text("Copy");

    // Load each JavaScript file after the page has loaded
    function loadScript(url) {
        var url = 'https://players.brightcove.net/3588749423001/default_default/index.min.js';
        var deferred = $.Deferred();
        var script = document.createElement('script');
        script.src = url;
        
        // Add an event listener to resolve the promise when the script is loaded
        script.onload = function() {
            deferred.resolve();
        };
        
        // Add the script to the body to start loading it
        document.body.appendChild(script);
        
        // Return the promise
        return deferred.promise();
    }

    function load_js() {
        var deferred = $.Deferred();
        var head = document.getElementsByTagName('head')[0];
        var script = document.createElement('script');
        script.type = 'text/javascript';
        script.src = "https://www.bcci.tv/js/bcciplayer.js?v=2.6";
        // Add an event listener to resolve the promise when the script is loaded
        script.onload = function() {
            deferred.resolve();
        };
        
        head.appendChild(script);
        
        // Return the promise
        return deferred.promise();
    }
    $(document).on("click", ".playerpopup", function () {
        var t = window.location.href;
        var e = $(this).attr("data-videoId"),
            a = $(this).attr("data-duration"),
            r = ($(this).attr("data-duration1"), $(this).attr("data-mediaId")),
            o = $(this).attr("data-videoTitle"),
            i = $(this).attr("data-videoView"),
            n = $(this).attr("data-videoDate"),
            d = ($(this).attr("data-videoslug"), 
            desc=$(this).attr("data-short-description")),
            s = $(this).attr("data-share");
        if(playerStatus == false){
            playerStatus = true;
            load_js()
            .then(loadScript)
            .then(function() {
                PlayFun(t, e, a, r, o, i, n, d, desc, s);
            })
            .catch(function(error) {
                console.error("An error occurred while loading scripts:", error);
            });


        }else{
            PlayFun(t,e,a,r,o,i,n,d,desc,s);
        }
    });


    $(document).on("click", ".playerpage", function () {
            var t = $(this).attr("data-mediaId"),
            e = $(this).attr("data-videoId"),
            a = $(this).attr("data-videoTitle"),
            r = $(this).attr("data-description"),
            o = $(this).attr("data-short-description"),
            i = $(this).attr("data-videoView"),
            n = $(this).attr("data-videoDate"),
            d = $(this).attr("data-share"),
            s = ($(this).attr("data-thumbnile"), $(this).attr("data-duration")),
            c = ($(this).attr("data-duration1"), "");

        if(playerStatus == false){
            playerStatus = true;
            load_js()
            .then(loadScript)
            .then(function() {
                Playpage(t, e, a, r, o, i, n, d, s, c);
            })
            .catch(function(error) {
                console.error("An error occurred while loading scripts:", error);
            });


        }else{
            Playpage(t, e, a, r, o, i, n, d, s, c);
        }
    });
</script>

# Specify the URL
url = 'https://www.bcci.tv/'

# Send a GET request to the URL
response = requests.get(url)

# Check if the request was successful (status code 200)
if response.status_code == 200:
    # Parse the HTML content of the home page
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')

    # Find the link to the international fixtures page
    fixtures_link = soup.find('a', {'class': 'international-home'})

    if fixtures_link:
        # Construct the URL for the international fixtures page
        fixtures_url = 'https://www.bcci.tv' + fixtures_link['href']

        # Send a GET request to the international fixtures page
        fixtures_response = requests.get(fixtures_url)

        # Check if the request was successful (status code 200)
        if fixtures_response.status_code == 200:
            # Parse the HTML content of the international fixtures page
            fixtures_soup = BeautifulSoup(fixtures_response.text, 'html.parser')

            # Find and extract details of Team India's international fixtures
            fixtures_data = []
            fixtures_divs = fixtures_soup.find_all('div', {'class': 'fixture__info'})

            for fixture_div in fixtures_divs:
                series = fixture_div.find('span', {'class': 'u-unskewed-text'}).text.strip()
                place = fixture_div.find('p', {'class': 'fixture__additional-info'}).text.strip()
                date = fixture_div.find('span', {'class': 'fixture__date'}).text.strip()
                time = fixture_div.find('span', {'class': 'fixture__time'}).text.strip()

                fixtures_data.append({
                    'Series': series,
                    'Place': place,
                    'Date': date,
                    'Time': time
                })

            # Print or process the scraped fixture details
            for fixture in fixtures_data:
                print(f"A) Series: {fixture['Series']}")
                print(f"B) Place: {fixture['Place']}")
                print(f"C) Date: {fixture['Date']}")
                print(f"D) Time: {fixture['Time']}")
                print('\n')

        else:
            print(f'Error: Unable to fetch the international fixtures page. Status code: {fixtures_response.status_code}')

    else:
        print('Error: Could not find the link to the international fixtures page on the home page.')

else:
    print(f'Error: Unable to fetch the home page. Status code: {response.status_code}')

# Specify the URL
url = 'http://statisticstimes.com/'

# Send a GET request to the URL
response = requests.get(url)

# Check if the request was successful (status code 200)
if response.status_code == 200:
    # Parse the HTML content of the home page
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')

    # Find the link to the economy page
    economy_link = soup.find('a', {'title': 'Economy'})

    if economy_link:
        # Construct the URL for the economy page
        economy_url = 'http://statisticstimes.com/' + economy_link['href']

        # Send a GET request to the economy page
        economy_response = requests.get(economy_url)

        # Check if the request was successful (status code 200)
        if economy_response.status_code == 200:
            # Parse the HTML content of the economy page
            economy_soup = BeautifulSoup(economy_response.text, 'html.parser')

            # Find and extract details of State-wise GDP
            gdp_data = []
            table = economy_soup.find('table', {'id': 'table_id'})

            if table:
                rows = table.find_all('tr')[1:]  # Skip the header row
                for row in rows:
                    columns = row.find_all('td')
                    rank = columns[0].text.strip()
                    state = columns[1].text.strip()
                    gdp_18_19 = columns[2].text.strip()
                    gdp_19_20 = columns[3].text.strip()
                    share_18_19 = columns[4].text.strip()
                    gdp_billion = columns[5].text.strip()

                    gdp_data.append({
                        'Rank': rank,
                        'State': state,
                        'GSDP(18-19)': gdp_18_19,
                        'GSDP(19-20)': gdp_19_20,
                        'Share(18-19)': share_18_19,
                        'GDP($ billion)': gdp_billion
                    })

                # Print or process the scraped GDP details
                for data in gdp_data:
                    print(f"A) Rank: {data['Rank']}")
                    print(f"B) State: {data['State']}")
                    print(f"C) GSDP(18-19): {data['GSDP(18-19)']}")
                    print(f"D) GSDP(19-20): {data['GSDP(19-20)']}")
                    print(f"E) Share(18-19): {data['Share(18-19)']}")
                    print(f"F) GDP($ billion): {data['GDP($ billion)']}")
                    print('\n')

            else:
                print('Error: Unable to find the GDP table on the economy page.')

        else:
            print(f'Error: Unable to fetch the economy page. Status code: {economy_response.status_code}')

    else:
        print('Error: Could not find the link to the economy page on the home page.')

else:
    print(f'Error: Unable to fetch the home page. Status code: {response.status_code}')

Error: Could not find the link to the economy page on the home page.

# Specify the URL for the GitHub home page
github_home_url = 'https://github.com/'

# Send a GET request to the GitHub home page
response_home = requests.get(github_home_url)

# Check if the request to the home page was successful (status code 200)
if response_home.status_code == 200:
    # Parse the HTML content of the home page
    soup_home = BeautifulSoup(response_home.text, 'html.parser')

    # Find the link to the trending page in the Explore menu
    trending_link = soup_home.find('a', {'href': '/trending'})

    if trending_link:
        # Construct the URL for the trending page
        trending_url = 'https://github.com' + trending_link['href']

        # Send a GET request to the trending page
        response_trending = requests.get(trending_url)

        # Check if the request to the trending page was successful (status code 200)
        if response_trending.status_code == 200:
            # Parse the HTML content of the trending page
            soup_trending = BeautifulSoup(response_trending.text, 'html.parser')

            # Find and extract details of trending repositories
            repo_titles = []
            repo_descriptions = []
            contributors_counts = []
            languages_used = []

            # Locate the repositories using the updated class names
            repos = soup_trending.find_all('article', {'class': 'Box-row'})

            for repo in repos:
                # Repository title
                title_tag = repo.find('h1', {'class': 'h3 lh-condensed'})
                title = title_tag.text.strip() if title_tag else 'Title not available'
                repo_titles.append(title)

                # Repository description
                description_tag = repo.find('p', {'class': 'col-9 color-text-secondary my-1 pr-4'})
                description = description_tag.text.strip() if description_tag else 'Description not available'
                repo_descriptions.append(description)

                # Contributors count
                contributors_count_tag = repo.find('a', {'class': 'Link--muted d-inline-block mr-3'})
                contributors_count = contributors_count_tag.text.strip() if contributors_count_tag else 'Contributors count not available'
                contributors_counts.append(contributors_count)

                # Language used
                language_tag = repo.find('span', {'itemprop': 'programmingLanguage'})
                language_used = language_tag.text.strip() if language_tag else 'Language not available'
                languages_used.append(language_used)

            # Print or process the scraped repository details
            for i in range(len(repo_titles)):
                print(f"A) Repository title: {repo_titles[i]}")
                print(f"B) Repository description: {repo_descriptions[i]}")
                print(f"C) Contributors count: {contributors_counts[i]}")
                print(f"D) Language used: {languages_used[i]}")
                print('\n')

        else:
            print(f'Error: Unable to fetch the trending page. Status code: {response_trending.status_code}')

    else:
        print('Error: Could not find the link to the trending page in the Explore menu.')

else:
    print(f'Error: Unable to fetch the GitHub home page. Status code: {response_home.status_code}')

# Specify the URL for the Billboard home page
billboard_home_url = 'https://www.billboard.com/'

# Send a GET request to the Billboard home page
response_home = requests.get(billboard_home_url)

# Check if the request to the home page was successful (status code 200)
if response_home.status_code == 200:
    # Parse the HTML content of the home page
    soup_home = BeautifulSoup(response_home.text, 'html.parser')

    # Find the link to the Hot 100 page under the Charts option
    hot_100_link = soup_home.find('a', {'href': '/charts/hot-100'})

    if hot_100_link:
        # Construct the URL for the Hot 100 page
        hot_100_url = 'https://www.billboard.com' + hot_100_link['href']

        # Send a GET request to the Hot 100 page
        response_hot_100 = requests.get(hot_100_url)

        # Check if the request to the Hot 100 page was successful (status code 200)
        if response_hot_100.status_code == 200:
            # Parse the HTML content of the Hot 100 page
            soup_hot_100 = BeautifulSoup(response_hot_100.text, 'html.parser')

            # Find and extract details of the top 100 songs
            songs_data = []
            songs = soup_hot_100.find_all('li', {'class': 'chart-list__element'})

            for song in songs:
                # Song name
                song_name = song.find('span', {'class': 'chart-element__information__song text--truncate color--primary'}).text.strip()

                # Artist name
                artist_name = song.find('span', {'class': 'chart-element__information__artist text--truncate color--secondary'}).text.strip()

                # Last week rank
                last_week_rank = song.find('span', {'class': 'chart-element__meta text--center color--secondary text--last'}).text.strip()

                # Peak rank
                peak_rank = song.find('span', {'class': 'chart-element__meta text--center color--secondary text--peak'}).text.strip()

                # Weeks on board
                weeks_on_board = song.find('span', {'class': 'chart-element__meta text--center color--secondary text--week'}).text.strip()

                songs_data.append({
                    'Song Name': song_name,
                    'Artist Name': artist_name,
                    'Last Week Rank': last_week_rank,
                    'Peak Rank': peak_rank,
                    'Weeks on Board': weeks_on_board
                })

            # Print or process the scraped song details
            for i, song_data in enumerate(songs_data[:100]):
                print(f"{i + 1}) Song Name: {song_data['Song Name']}")
                print(f"   Artist Name: {song_data['Artist Name']}")
                print(f"   Last Week Rank: {song_data['Last Week Rank']}")
                print(f"   Peak Rank: {song_data['Peak Rank']}")
                print(f"   Weeks on Board: {song_data['Weeks on Board']}")
                print('\n')

        else:
            print(f'Error: Unable to fetch the Hot 100 page. Status code: {response_hot_100.status_code}')

    else:
        print('Error: Could not find the link to the Hot 100 page under the Charts option.')

else:
    print(f'Error: Unable to fetch the Billboard home page. Status code: {response_home.status_code}')

Error: Could not find the link to the Hot 100 page under the Charts option.

# Specify the URL
url = 'https://www.theguardian.com/news/datablog/2012/aug/09/best-selling-books-all-time-fifty-shades-grey-compare'

# Send a GET request to the URL
response = requests.get(url)

# Check if the request was successful (status code 200)
if response.status_code == 200:
    # Parse the HTML content of the page
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')

    # Find the table containing the highest-selling novels data
    novels_table = soup.find('table', {'class': 'in-article sortable'})

    if novels_table:
        # Extract data from the table
        novels_data = []
        rows = novels_table.find_all('tr')[1:]  # Skip the header row

        for row in rows:
            columns = row.find_all('td')

            # Check the length of the columns list to avoid IndexError
            if len(columns) >= 5:
                book_name = columns[0].text.strip()
                author_name = columns[1].text.strip()
                volumes_sold = columns[2].text.strip()
                publisher = columns[3].text.strip()
                genre = columns[4].text.strip()

                novels_data.append({
                    'Book Name': book_name,
                    'Author Name': author_name,
                    'Volumes Sold': volumes_sold,
                    'Publisher': publisher,
                    'Genre': genre
                })

        # Print or process the scraped novel details
        for i, novel_data in enumerate(novels_data):
            print(f"{i + 1}) Book Name: {novel_data['Book Name']}")
            print(f"   Author Name: {novel_data['Author Name']}")
            print(f"   Volumes Sold: {novel_data['Volumes Sold']}")
            print(f"   Publisher: {novel_data['Publisher']}")
            print(f"   Genre: {novel_data['Genre']}")
            print('\n')

    else:
        print('Error: Unable to find the novels table on the page.')

else:
    print(f'Error: Unable to fetch the URL. Status code: {response.status_code}')

Q7.¶

In [19]:
# Specify the URL
url = 'https://www.imdb.com/list/ls512407256/'

# Send a GET request to the URL
response = requests.get(url)

# Check if the request was successful (status code 200)
if response.status_code == 200:
    # Parse the HTML content of the page
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')

    # Find the list of TV series
    series_list = soup.find_all('div', {'class': 'lister-item-content'})

    # Extract data from each TV series
    tv_series_data = []
    for series in series_list:
        # Name
        name = series.find('h3', {'class': 'lister-item-header'}).a.text.strip()

        # Year span
        year_span = series.find('span', {'class': 'lister-item-year'}).text.strip()

        # Genre
        genre = series.find('span', {'class': 'genre'}).text.strip()

        # Run time
        run_time = series.find('span', {'class': 'runtime'}).text.strip()

        # Ratings
        ratings = series.find('span', {'class': 'ipl-rating-star__rating'}).text.strip()

        # Votes
        votes = series.find('span', {'name': 'nv'}).text.strip()

        tv_series_data.append({
            'Name': name,
            'Year Span': year_span,
            'Genre': genre,
            'Run Time': run_time,
            'Ratings': ratings,
            'Votes': votes
        })

    # Print or process the scraped TV series details
    for i, series_data in enumerate(tv_series_data):
        print(f"{i + 1}) Name: {series_data['Name']}")
        print(f"   Year Span: {series_data['Year Span']}")
        print(f"   Genre: {series_data['Genre']}")
        print(f"   Run Time: {series_data['Run Time']}")
        print(f"   Ratings: {series_data['Ratings']}")
        print(f"   Votes: {series_data['Votes']}")
        print('\n')

else:
    print(f'Error: Unable to fetch the URL. Status code: {response.status_code}')

# Specify the URL for the UCI Machine Learning Repository home page
uci_home_url = 'https://archive.ics.uci.edu/'

# Send a GET request to the UCI home page
response_home = requests.get(uci_home_url)

# Check if the request to the home page was successful (status code 200)
if response_home.status_code == 200:
    # Parse the HTML content of the home page
    soup_home = BeautifulSoup(response_home.text, 'html.parser')

    # Find the link to the "Show All Dataset" page
    show_all_datasets_link = soup_home.find('a', {'href': '/ml/datasets.php'})

    if show_all_datasets_link:
        # Construct the URL for the "Show All Dataset" page
        show_all_datasets_url = uci_home_url + show_all_datasets_link['href']

        # Send a GET request to the "Show All Dataset" page
        response_show_all_datasets = requests.get(show_all_datasets_url)

        # Check if the request to the "Show All Dataset" page was successful (status code 200)
        if response_show_all_datasets.status_code == 200:
            # Parse the HTML content of the "Show All Dataset" page
            soup_show_all_datasets = BeautifulSoup(response_show_all_datasets.text, 'html.parser')

            # Find and extract details of datasets
            datasets_data = []
            datasets_table = soup_show_all_datasets.find('table', {'border': '1'})

            if datasets_table:
                rows = datasets_table.find_all('tr')[1:]  # Skip the header row

                for row in rows:
                    columns = row.find_all('td')

                    # Dataset name
                    dataset_name = columns[0].text.strip()

                    # Data type
                    data_type = columns[1].text.strip()

                    # Task
                    task = columns[2].text.strip()

                    # Attribute type
                    attribute_type = columns[3].text.strip()

                    # Number of instances
                    num_instances = columns[4].text.strip()

                    # Number of attributes
                    num_attributes = columns[5].text.strip()

                    # Year
                    year = columns[6].text.strip()

                    datasets_data.append({
                        'Dataset Name': dataset_name,
                        'Data Type': data_type,
                        'Task': task,
                        'Attribute Type': attribute_type,
                        'No of Instances': num_instances,
                        'No of Attributes': num_attributes,
                        'Year': year
                    })

            # Print or process the scraped dataset details
            for i, dataset_data in enumerate(datasets_data):
                print(f"{i + 1}) Dataset Name: {dataset_data['Dataset Name']}")
                print(f"   Data Type: {dataset_data['Data Type']}")
                print(f"   Task: {dataset_data['Task']}")
                print(f"   Attribute Type: {dataset_data['Attribute Type']}")
                print(f"   No of Instances: {dataset_data['No of Instances']}")
                print(f"   No of Attributes: {dataset_data['No of Attributes']}")
                print(f"   Year: {dataset_data['Year']}")
                print('\n')

        else:
            print(f'Error: Unable to fetch the "Show All Dataset" page. Status code: {response_show_all_datasets.status_code}')

    else:
        print('Error: Could not find the link to the "Show All Dataset" page.')

else:
    print(f'Error: Unable to fetch the UCI home page. Status code: {response_home.status_code}')

Error: Could not find the link to the "Show All Dataset" page.
